reviews.title: READ READ
reviews.review_text: I've read a lot of reviews that say these aren't good or they peel easy. Well I don't think they read the directions/instructions correctly. First off, it says these are not oven safe. 2nd, you have SEASON the pans prior to your first use. So you wash them with soap and warm water they dry them. Spread oil on a paper towel or clean rag and rub inside the pan. Then heat them over medium heat for 2-3 mins each. Then wash with soap and warm water. These are aluminum so it heats up pretty quickly so there's no need to go over medium heat. These cannot be used with high heat. And don't spray nonstick spray on them. it'll make them crust up. They're not that small. Everyone was making it seem like they're mini and they're alight. Not for big families though. Don't use tuff, abrasive, steel wool, or coarse cleaning scrubs/pads. Always turn the handles away from heat or where heat is gathered. Don't use in a broiler. Always let the pans cool before washing to prolong them. Recommended cooking utensils are nylon, bamboo , or wood to prolong and keep from scratching. Read all the instructions before your first use and you'll be fine.

The pots and pans cook well - no burns or hot spots. Clean up is very easy. I have not put them in the dishwasher yet so I have been washing/drying them by hand after use and cooled down. The cooking utensils were a nice touch as I did need some new ones. The only downside I wish there was a whisk instead of three spoons or two spatulas. Perfect set for a single person or a kind of small family. If that is what you need I would suggest looking for a high capacity set.
